{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bab571a9-9e31-412a-a122-b557da52812f","content":"**Exit code 8** means \"zero tests ran.\" Microsoft.Testing.Platform treats this as a failure by default, unlike VSTest.\n\nThe fix is the new MSBuild property:\n\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformShowTestsFailure>false</TestingPlatformShowTestsFailure>\n```\n\nThis tells the runner that discovering zero tests is **not** a failure, so it returns exit code 0 instead of 8. Your conditionally-compiled assemblies (like `ConditionalTests.cs` behind `#if INCLUDE_SLOW_TESTS`) will no longer break CI when they produce no tests.\n\nYou can also pass this at the command line per-run: `--minimum-expected-tests 0`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e5d12f55-b7c9-4413-9bd1-4ab1aa8403e0","outputTokens":168,"requestId":"4814:12FCC3:31CF8BC:3670538:69FBE443"},"id":"d5aa9d51-f0c8-4543-a8a8-0bc1ed69a005","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:00:58.812Z","parentId":"6fc4ec8f-6777-43d6-9b11-43486d001e58"}
